# Interview-IQ Project

Interview prep tracker: users log LeetCode-style problems, get a score per attempt, scores decay over time (simulating forgetting), and a radar chart shows per-category skill strength.

## Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Backend | Go 1.26, Chi v5, PostgreSQL 16, `database/sql` + `lib/pq` (no ORM) |
| Auth | JWT HS256 (7-day), bcrypt |
| Frontend | React 19, Vite, TypeScript strict, ShadCN/UI, Recharts, Axios, React Router |

## Repository Structure

```
interview-iq/
├── backend/
│   ├── cmd/server/main.go          # Entry point: env, DI wiring, Chi router
│   ├── internal/
│   │   ├── auth/jwt.go             # Token generation + parsing
│   │   ├── db/                     # Connection pool + migration runner
│   │   ├── handlers/               # HTTP handlers (thin — decode → service → respond)
│   │   ├── middleware/auth.go      # JWT validation, UserIDFromContext
│   │   ├── models/                 # Plain structs + score/decay logic
│   │   ├── repository/             # SQL implementations of repo interfaces
│   │   └── service/                # Business logic + validation
│   └── migrations/                 # Numbered SQL files (001_init.sql, ...)
└── frontend/                       # Vite + React (to be scaffolded)
    └── src/
        ├── pages/                  # Route-level components
        ├── components/             # Reusable components; ui/ = ShadCN (don't edit)
        ├── lib/api.ts              # Axios instance with JWT interceptor
        ├── hooks/                  # Custom React hooks
        └── types/                  # TS types mirroring API response shapes
```

## Score Model (critical — never change without updating tests)

- `ComputeScore(attempts, lookedAtSolution)` — called **once at write time**, stored in DB
- `ApplyDecay(score, solvedAt)` — called **at read time only**, never persisted
- Grace period: 3 days; decay: 2pts/day after grace; floor: 30% of original score

